# HANDCRAFTED QUALITY SECTION

## Section Title
The Process: How We Work

## Content

Every Javier's Furniture 13:20 piece is handcrafted in our workshop, where modern precision tools work in harmony with traditional hand techniques.

Javier personally oversees each stage of creation, from initial wood selection through final finishing. This is not mass production. This is dedicated craftsmanship in service of something larger than profit.

### The Timeline

We don't rush. Here's why:

1. **Wood Selection & Acclimation** (1-2 weeks)
   Raw wood is selected, inspected, and allowed to acclimate to local humidity and temperature. This prevents warping and ensures stability.

2. **Design & Planning** (1-2 weeks)
   Sketches are drawn. Every joint is planned. Every detail is considered. Traditional joinery is mapped out precisely.

3. **Rough Milling** (1 week)
   The wood is shaped and prepared, following the grain and respecting the tree's natural structure.

4. **Joinery Work** (1-3 weeks)
   The most skilled work. Mortises are cut. Tenons are shaped. Dovetails are hand-cut and fitted. This cannot be rushed.

5. **Assembly & Gluing** (1 week)
   Pieces are assembled dry first to ensure perfect fit. Then, with natural wood glue, the joints are made permanent.

6. **Finishing** (2-4 weeks)
   Surfaces are hand-planed, sanded, and finished with natural oils or hand-rubbed wax. Multiple coats. Time between each for curing.

7. **Quality Inspection** (1 week)
   Every inch is examined. Every joint is tested. Every finish is evaluated. Only perfect pieces leave the workshop.

### Why This Matters

When you bring a Javier's Furniture 13:20 piece into your home, you are welcoming a fragment of the Mayan Jungle, transformed through artisan skill into functional beauty.

This is furniture as ceremony. This is wood as teacher. This is the Creator's work made visible through human hands.

This is the Javier's Furniture 13:20 promise: furniture that honors its origins, celebrates the craftsman's art, and becomes an integral part of your life's most meaningful moments.

